INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES (1,2,'House vs Home','Hi everyone! I’ve been wondering about the difference between the words house and home. When do you typically use one over the other? Are there specific contexts or nuances that make one more appropriate than the other? I’d love to hear your thoughts and examples!',0,'2024-11-25 15:56:11','2024-11-25 15:56:11'),(2,4,'What does \"apple\" mean?','Can somebody tell me what does \"apple\" mean?',0,'2024-11-25 16:34:08','2024-11-25 16:34:08'),(3,1,'What Does \"Angry\" Mean?','Hi everyone! 😊\n\nI’m trying to understand the word \"angry.\" How is it used in English, and how would you translate it into Turkish? I think it means \"kızgın\" or \"öfkeli,\" but I’d like to see examples in both languages to understand it better.\n\nThanks for your help! 🙏',0,'2024-11-25 16:47:42','2024-11-25 16:47:42'),(4,1,'Meaning of \"Furious\"?','Hi, can someone explain \"furious\" and give a Turkish translation with examples?',0,'2024-11-25 16:49:56','2024-11-25 16:49:56'),(5,4,'An apple a day keeps the doctor away.','I was wondering what does \"an apple a day keeps the doctor away\" mean?',0,'2024-11-25 17:00:02','2024-11-25 17:00:02'),(6,11,'Bridge','what does bridge mean?',0,'2024-11-25 18:58:55','2024-11-25 18:58:55'),(8,2,'The usage of “fight” vs. “battle” etc.','Hi everyone! 😊\nI\'m curious about the word \"fight\" and its synonyms. For example, when should I use \"fight\" instead of words like \"battle,\" \"struggle,\" or \"quarrel\"? Are they interchangeable, or do they have specific contexts? I also wonder if \"fight\" always means something physical or if it can describe emotional or verbal conflicts too.\n\nCould you share examples of how these words are used in daily conversations or in writing? Thank you! 🙏',0,'2024-11-26 11:11:51','2024-11-26 11:11:51'),(9,12,'Help me use “magic” in a sentence','Hi everyone! 😊\nI’m learning about the word \"magic\" and its uses. I made a sentence, but I’m not sure if it sounds correct:\n\n\"The sunset was so beautiful, it looked like magic was flying in the air.\"\n\nDoes this use of \"magic\" make sense, or is there a better way to describe the feeling? Can \"magic\" be used this way, or does it sound strange? I’d love your feedback and examples! Thank you! 🙏',0,'2024-11-26 11:20:39','2024-11-26 11:20:39'),(10,2,'How to use “beautiful” ?','Hi all!! \n\nI’m learning how to use the word \"beautiful\" in different contexts. I made this sentence:\n\n\"The mountain view was so beautiful that it made me cry.\"\n\nDoes this sound natural, or could there be a better way to express the feeling? Also, can \"beautiful\" only describe things like nature or people, or can it describe abstract things like a \"beautiful idea\"? I’d love to hear your thoughts and examples. Thank you! 🙏',0,'2024-11-26 11:45:22','2024-11-26 11:45:22'),(11,7,'How Do I Use \"Ineffable\" Correctly?','I\'ve recently come across the word ineffable and understand it means something too great or extreme to be expressed in words. Could someone provide examples of how this word might be used in sentences? Also, how does it compare to words like indescribable or unspeakable?',0,'2024-11-26 12:13:22','2024-11-26 12:13:22'),(12,7,'Obfuscate vs. Confuse—What\'s the Difference?','I understand obfuscate means to make something unclear or difficult to understand, but how does it differ from simply saying \"confuse\"? Can someone share examples to clarify its usage?',0,'2024-11-26 12:14:00','2024-11-26 12:14:00'),(13,7,'How Does \"Ephemeral\" Compare to \"Temporary\"?','I’ve seen ephemeral used to describe things that are short-lived, but is it just a fancy way of saying \"temporary\"? Are there situations where one is more appropriate than the other? Examples would help!',0,'2024-11-26 12:14:35','2024-11-26 12:14:35'),(14,7,'\"Ineffable\" in Everyday Conversations','I’ve noticed that ineffable is often used in poetic or formal contexts, but can it also be applied in everyday conversations? For instance, could I use it to describe a delicious meal or a fun day with friends? I’d love examples or opinions on when it feels appropriate to use this word casually.',0,'2024-11-26 12:24:23','2024-11-26 12:24:23'),(15,3,'Ambition and Hope','Can someone explain the difference between \'ambition\' and \'hope\'? They both seem to involve wanting something in the future.',0,'2024-11-26 12:42:43','2024-11-26 12:42:43'),(16,3,'Journey, Trip, Voyage','I’m confused about the word \'journey.\' How is it different from \'trip\' or \'voyage\'?',0,'2024-11-26 12:43:55','2024-11-26 12:43:55'),(17,3,'About Serene','\"What’s the exact meaning of \'serene\'? Does it only describe people, or can it describe places too?\"',0,'2024-11-26 12:44:21','2024-11-26 12:44:21'),(31,3,'Elephant and Tiger','Are the Turkish translations for Elephant(Fil) and Tiger(Kaplan) accurate? Anyone confirm or suggest alternatives?',0,'2024-12-16 19:01:53','2024-12-16 19:01:53'),(68,24,'What are the different uses of the word \"shield\"?','Hi everyone,\n\nI recently came across the word \"shield,\" and I noticed it can be used in different contexts. Could someone explain the various ways this word is used? For example, I\'ve seen it used both as a noun and a verb.',0,'2024-12-16 19:07:40','2024-12-16 19:07:40'),(76,3,'Baharat - Spice','For \'spice\', does the Turkish translation \'baharat\' align with regional variations? Is there a better term?',0,'2024-12-16 19:16:22','2024-12-16 19:16:22'),(77,3,'Recipe uses','Is the word \'recipe\' only used in food context? I feel like I heard the phrase \"This is a recipe for disaster\" in a movie. What does that mean?\nSorry for bad english.',0,'2024-12-16 19:20:26','2024-12-16 19:20:26'),(78,3,'Oven Confuses Me','Man, I confuse \'Oven\' with refrigerator all the time. When I think about the word \'Oven\', always the image of a refrigerator(buz dolabi) comes to my mind. Does that happen to you guys also? Am I a silly goose?',0,'2024-12-16 19:22:50','2024-12-16 19:22:50'),(79,3,'Red is color?','I thought we said red when we are saying like:\n\"Hey, I red a book today.\"\nIs it also a color? I\'m confused',0,'2024-12-16 19:27:24','2024-12-16 19:27:24'),(80,3,'Is dog a bad word?','This might be a sensitive question. Calling someone \"kopek\" in Turkish is bad. Is it the same way \"dog\" in English?\nThank you for your understanding.',0,'2024-12-16 19:30:44','2024-12-16 19:30:44'),(81,3,'\"At\" meaning in turkish','I thought \"At\" meant \"thow\". This other question says it means \"horse\". Does it have two meanings? Can you tell me if it has any more meanings?',0,'2024-12-16 19:33:36','2024-12-16 19:33:36'),(82,1,'What Does \"Acceleration\" Mean to You?','What does the word “acceleration” remind you of? How would you explain it in your own words?',0,'2024-12-16 23:01:29','2024-12-16 23:01:29'),(83,1,'How Do You Use the Word \"Accelerator\"?','When you hear the word “accelerator”, what comes to mind first? Can you think of a situation where you’ve seen or used this word?',0,'2024-12-16 23:01:50','2024-12-16 23:01:50'),(84,24,'What is the exact meaning of \"apartment\"?','I’ve come across the word \"apartment\" a lot, and I know it refers to a place where people live, but I’m curious about its specific usage.\n\nIs there a difference between \"apartment\" and \"flat\"?\n\nThanks!\n',0,'2024-12-17 06:43:13','2024-12-17 06:43:13'),(85,24,'Can \"subway\" have different meanings?','I noticed that the word \"subway\" might have more than one meaning depending on the region. For instance:\nIn the United States, it refers to an underground train system.\n\nExample: \"The New York subway is one of the largest in the world.\"\nIn the UK, I’ve heard it can also mean an underground pedestrian tunnel.\n\nExample: \"We walked through the subway to cross the busy road.\"\n\nDoes anyone know any other regional differences or unusual uses of this word? Are there specific phrases or sentences where \"subway\" is commonly used?\n\n',0,'2024-12-17 06:45:57','2024-12-17 06:45:57'),(86,24,'Another word instead of library','Hi. I want to know if there is another word I can use instead of Library. Do you know any?',0,'2024-12-17 06:48:12','2024-12-17 06:48:12'),(87,24,'Difference between educational Places','School vs High School vs Elementary School vs College vs University\n\nYou guys know the difference between them? I know sth but I am not sure about it.',0,'2024-12-17 06:51:03','2024-12-17 06:51:03'),(88,24,'Masjid vs Mosque','Although I don\'t know the technical differences between these two words, I think it\'s like this: A mosque has a pulpit, but a masjid doesn\'t. And of course, a mosque is usually much bigger than a masjid. Am I right?',0,'2024-12-17 06:53:38','2024-12-17 06:53:38'),(89,24,'How is the word \"park\" used in different contexts?','Hi everyone!\n\nThe word \"park\" seems simple at first, but I’ve noticed it can be used in several different ways. For example:\n\nAs a noun: A public place for relaxation or activities.\nExample: \"We had a picnic in the park yesterday.\"\n\nAs a verb: To leave a vehicle in a particular spot.\nExample: \"You can park your car near the entrance.\"\n\nAre there other meanings or phrases where \"park\" is used? \n\nThanks!',0,'2024-12-17 06:56:50','2024-12-17 06:56:50'),(90,24,'Common types of structures','I’ve been learning words related to structures and I realized there are so many different types, like:\n\nBridge – \"The bridge connects the two sides of the river.\"\nSkyscraper – \"The skyscraper is the tallest building in the city.\"\nTunnel – \"The train went through a long tunnel.\"\n\n\nAre there other common structure-related words that I should know? With examples.\n\nI am waiting your answers.',0,'2024-12-17 06:59:43','2024-12-17 06:59:43'),(91,24,'What are some ways we can describe connections between two places?','Hello guys!\n\nI’ve been thinking about different ways we describe connections between two locations, and there are so many ways to do it. Here are a few examples:\n\nLink: \"The road links the two towns.\"\nPathway: \"The pathway leads from the park to the museum.\"\nRoute: \"This route connects the airport to the city center.\"\n\nHow else do you describe the idea of connecting places? Are there any other words or phrases that work in different contexts?\n\nLooking forward to your responses!',0,'2024-12-17 07:10:46','2024-12-17 07:10:46'),(92,21,'Bridge example','Hello Students. I hope you enjoyed our quiz. \n\nNow, please give me an example sentence of the word \"bridge\".',0,'2024-12-17 07:43:24','2024-12-17 07:43:24'),(93,24,'Bridge exampe','The bridge was built to connect the two sides of the river, making travel much easier for the villagers.\n\nI wrote this sentence. Can anyone confirm it?',0,'2024-12-17 07:48:04','2024-12-17 07:48:04');
